snippet.title: Foreplay
snippet.description: He walks around, finding girls from subway stations to park benches, handing out cards that advertise his ability to provide "Honey, Rose Petels (sic), Candles, and Bubble Baths." Rejection followed him at every turn, until one day he met a girl who couldn't take her eyes off him. A girl whose jaw remained permanently agape at the boldness of his offer.

snippet.title: Handicapable
snippet.description: Jan's Weirdling abilities extended further, allowing her to cook Rice-A-Roni 1.5x faster and to always have a classic Milton Berle joke on hand for any given situation. But they didn't extend much further than that.

snippet.title: A BP Oil Executive Gets Iced
snippet.description: Had British Petroleum bothered to research the "Bros Icing Bros" phenomenon, this horrible disaster could have been averted. Sadly, their ignorance was our loss, as we were forced to watch a high-ranking executive at the troubled company chug an excruciating amount of malt liquor, with absolutely no clear way to stop it.

snippet.title: Irresponsible Patriot
snippet.description: The combustibility of Premium brand beer is in sharp contrast to beers with low kerosene content, like your garden-variety pilsners or your mostly pedestrian lagers. In fact, a six-pack of Premium can get a commercial-size 18-wheeler over the hill on Highway 17 in Northern California. We discovered this fact during last year's 4OJ and frankly can't stop siphoning beer out of our gas tanks.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #223
snippet.description: Roid-rage fueled gun activists yearn for the days when "college ruled" and Hollywood agents and studios didn't just rely on a slew of unimaginative, violent, procedural cop shows.

snippet.title: Police Line
snippet.description: Warning: Boobsticks is still at large and considered extremely dangerous. If you have encountered Boobsticks, and you didn't have a machete handy, then you are dead and we're sorry Boobsticks killed you instead of old age.

snippet.title: Powered By Dreams
snippet.description: ​Back when California had those "rolling blackouts" to conserve power, Hollywood still glowed nice and bright, like a beacon of despair perched on a shining hill of shit. Mostly because there was a pretty huge casting call for That's So Raven.

snippet.title: More Behind The Scenes Action 1/21 - 1/25
snippet.description: Poo jokes. Just poo jokes. And even when the jokes aren't about poo, really, you can trace them back to poo somehow.

snippet.title: Chad "Tank" Ridderson's First Day at Work
snippet.description: Chad went on to overcome his deep sentimental attachment to those halcyon days of bodyshots, drunken stand-up paddleboard races and second-story ziplines, and he quickly rose up the ranks at SkremCorp. Promotion after promotion, Chad never lost sight of who he was, keeping that green notebook in his increasingly large, oaken desks wherever he went. As he grew older, it became a beacon of inspiration to himself and to many a Bro Hire that came through the SkremCorp doors. No one ever knew the contents of that seemingly magical notebook but Chad, and they were but a mere 11 words: "Have Dad Bribe My Superiors So I Don't Ever Get Fired."

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week 1/21 - 1/25
snippet.description:
5sf reads and answers your comments! Plus we launch a DONATE page because we are broke and can't buy any more props or beer! http://5secondfilms.com/donate
Special guest James Ashby from Saturday Morning Breakfast Serial Theater!
http://www.youtube.com/user/smbctheater

snippet.title: Studies Show
snippet.description: 9/10 is considered "The Golden Ratio" amongst the scientist-recommendation community. But every now and then, there is a tenth scientist who will not disagree - and they must be thinned from the herd. This process is called "Cresting," named after the infamous 10th dentist who couldn't bring himself to prefer Brand X over Crest Extra Whitening.

snippet.title: Power Lunch
snippet.description: Side effects to being this mega-shredded are as follows: Increased chance of heart failure, rage-cagin' city-wide rampages, and an inability to hold down any job other than lecturing high school assemblies on fitness by blowing up hot water bottles with just your lungpower.

snippet.title: Not OK!
snippet.description: A source close to Kelsey says, "He's a Leo, which contrasts with her sign. She wants a baby and he can't commit. He's jealous of her fame and they fight constantly. Any other fabricated, cotton candy, uninteresting, C-level soap opera, regurgitated bullshit you want me to spout about these two horrible people I've never met? How many pages do you have to fill before you get to Fashion Police?" Ms. Gunn's publicist could not be reached for comment, probably because we didn't even ask in the first place, since having no comment somehow makes for "juicier" drama.

snippet.title: Magnum π
snippet.description: Most of the time, he just shakes mathletes down for drug money. This is the most action he's gotten in weeks.

snippet.title: Nothing To Eat
snippet.description: Mischevio the Fridgegnome was out of ammo after that. He tried using the two-year-old hot sauce in the upper shelf of the fridge door, but nobody touched that stuff and neither, he tragically came to realize, would he.

snippet.title: The Big Move
snippet.description: Moving in a SmartCar makes you 140x better at Tetris. In some cases, you can even drive into the elevator and park right outside your new apartment door.

snippet.title: Rat Trap
snippet.description: In order to make the parts necessary for an oversized trap, the rats gathered together in the shape of a human, clambered into a suit, and traipsed down to the Silver Spring lumberyard. Unfortunately, their cover was blown, as any human knows you don't wear a suit to a lumberyard, and the rats dispersed immediately. They just wound up buying a pre-made trap off of eBay.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #222
snippet.description: While riding the rails through Mexico a hungry officer worker was sucked into a comfy couch with his poker player lesbian friends.

snippet.title: Slayer
snippet.description: Can you change a lesbian? Should you change a lesbian? Isn't it completely none of your business whether you can or can't change a person who loves the person she wants to love? The answers are yes, yes, and no, but only if you can beat her four-of-a-kind.

snippet.title: Comfy Couch
snippet.description: You didn't "lose" your car keys in there for four hours. They were borrowed by your alternate universe friends to help move some a new bed into an apartment a few blocks down the couch. Also, speaking of which, remember how there used to be a rollout bed attached to the couch? Well...you weren't using it.

snippet.title: Another Day at the Office
snippet.description: Fellow employees describe him as "cheerful," "easy to get along with," "attentive and focused," "comes in late on Mondays," and "eats shit." Needless to say, he passed the annual review with flying colors.

snippet.title: Montezuma's Revenge
snippet.description: Kelsey's not wrong - after all, ​"Montezuma" is Nahuatl for "Master Cleanse." Not many people know that, primarily because I made it up. So really, only I knew it. But since it's not a fact, I didn't exactly "know" it either. And since I knew something that isn't real, that means I'm not real, either. So, goodbye then. It's been fun.

snippet.title: Ol' Rail Riding Rodney
snippet.description: On account 'a being a skeleton since the days of President James Madison, Ol' Rodney's seen some things you people wouldn't darn near believe. Merchant ships on fire off the shoulder of Fort Sumter. He's watched I-beams clatter in the dark abandoned factories near the Hooverville Gates. And because his eternal soul won't shut up about none of it, all them there moments will be preserved in time, like bones in the dirt!

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 1/14 - 1/18
snippet.description: Howdy-doody. This week, we engage in a series of truly terrible puns, get some dog exercises in, confess what our middle names are, try in vain to defend our inclusion of black people in 5sfs, and travel at the speed of light.

snippet.title: What Mel Said
snippet.description:
As you can see, it takes us a little while to savage pop culture news so excellently, because getting the perfect joke is just worth it.

You know, the sad truth is, Mel Gibson is a good enough filmmaker to have made a better 5sf about this whole thing.

snippet.title: Dude Magnet
snippet.description: She read "The Game." She knows what's up. Now it's time to select a mark from the group, demonstrate her value, establish kino, and ditch the baby in a swing somewhere while they go make out behind a Red Robin.

snippet.title: Beach Party
snippet.description: I know what some of you might say. "How could any party be lame with Kelsey and Olivia there?" Well, they were talking about Spanx for the better part of three hours, and insisted on an all-Van Morrison party soundtrack. So there's your answer, internet.

snippet.title: Hungover Barber Shop Quartet
snippet.description: Their gig at Rudy's Senior Discount Summer Nights Bash got really out of hand. D'Artagnan did a keg stand off of the barbasol tank, Jensen mainlined a thick stream of heroin for two minutes straight, Aloysious saw into another dimension and Franklin became a bullgod.

snippet.title: New To The Neighborhood
snippet.description: The community frowned on his coaching the little league baseball team, particularly since their name was the Willing Duplicates.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #221
snippet.description: A drunk wingman at a study party got a winning ticket when a fortune teller told him what would be in tomorrow's paper.

snippet.title: Making The Paper
snippet.description:
Ever since all the nice girls started blogging and tweeting, it seems like only the mean nasty girls are left in print media. Good thing it's dying off anyway.

Special Guests, the ladies from Words With Girls!
http://www.youtube.com/user/WordsWithGirls

snippet.title: Fortune Teller
snippet.description: Always make sure to ask your Fortune Teller for precise clarification as to who, or what exactly, your wife may be seeing. If it's a turnip, or a Bachman Turner Overdrive reunion, or another man, or a shellfish & bluegrass festival, or perhaps someone in the room besides you, you won't know until you ask.

snippet.title: Winning Ticket
snippet.description: The winnings totaled somewhere around $300,000,000. It wasn't enough to beat his boss' legal team when they successfully argued that placing the ticket on her desk amounted to "gifting" her with it. The only silver lining to his dark cloud: Her legal team cost $299,999,991.23, which meant she still had to fish through her purse for change when she bought a slice of victory pie that night.

snippet.title: Study Party
snippet.description: He had a killer final the next day. Using his knowledge of physics, he absolutely nailed the beer pong section, but Professor Brodacious wound up giving him an F when fellow students accused him of being a nerd and using physics.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 1/7 - 1/11
snippet.description:
Enter the promo code WEAREBROKE at the checkout page to receive 15% off any item in the store, over the next week! http://store.5secondfilms.com

Also hear us rant about Paula Poundstone, crazy things that have been said to US during sex, and the appropriate way to bait a hook!

snippet.title: The Ultimate Wingman
snippet.description: ​He's since improved from his old wingmanning days, but get a few drinks in him and he'll still wind up telling people all about what a tender lover you are - except now he tells it to the dudes he's just punched in the face, which is a step up I guess.

snippet.title: The Nutritionist
snippet.description: Faster than a cayenne pepper-inspired bowel movement. More powerful than a fish diet rich in anti-oxidants! Able to leap tall stacks of health magazines with theories and research that cancel each other out...in a single bound!

snippet.title: Barry Ouelettes Video Resume
snippet.description: Frustrated at the lack of job opportunities for skilled lovers who've been around the block a few times and know a few things about life that some fancy schmancy degree can't teach you, Barry contacted a local video productions company to track him over the course of a wild, hellish couple of decades, in the efforts to document his whole life's work and perhaps one day pitch himself as a roadie for Eddie Money's tour -- truly, the greatest job Barry could think of at the time.

snippet.title: Last Words
snippet.description: His will left his AHHHHHHH to his GGGBBBBB(radio static). The family lawyer could do nothing about it.

snippet.title: The Ol' "Snakes In A Peanut Can" Trick
snippet.description: Marks Toys sold these "Snake'm Prank'm Cans" for one glorious summer in 1984, and ever since they discontinued production, it's become something of a collector's item. Mainly in Thailand, for whatever reason.

snippet.title: A Fat Kid Mulls His Options
snippet.description: After this, it's time to pick a pair of cargo shorts, Tivas, and trim the facial hair until only the neckbeard remains unshaven. And then it's time to troll the internet.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #220
snippet.description: Mr Silly woke up to the feeling of a hand up his ass from a person who's name he couldn't remember and whether or not he was paid up.

snippet.title: Joey Stromboli's
snippet.description: This is the second time his money laundering front has gone under before it even started. First time, it was a "Fluff-n-food" "restaurandromat" that failed to attract customers who wanted a great chicken parm while their whites were in the dryer. The organized crime families didn't even need to blow that one up. They just sat in lawn chairs across the street, watching Joey slowly go out of business through binoculars.

snippet.title: What's My Name?
snippet.description: Winners of the "What's My Name?" game receive a year's supply of rejection, dinner for one at the Couples In Love Spa/Resort, and a round trip to Isolation Hills with air travel provided by Virgin Atlantic.

snippet.title: Hand In Hand
snippet.description: They've never really completed a high-five. Not at a baseball game, not at an international high-five competition (they lost), not even at their own wedding.

snippet.title: Rock Around The Alarm Clock Rock
snippet.description: Sometimes he sets his drummer for 7:30 PM by accident, and the whole neighborhood basically gets to hear "Moby Dick" for 4 hours until he gets home.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 12/31 - 1/4
snippet.description:
The New Year has officially been rung in! Join us as we debate Salman Rushdie's career, whip out a few spankin' new puns and songs, take a peek into a vicious-sounding flame war, open more of your awesome packages and letters, and welcome one of the Mantle4Mantle finalists to the program!

Also features a dog penis.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #219
snippet.description: The final countdown at a New Year's party brings several resolutions about sex toys and meatball puns but then the scumbag meme cops came and beat the shit out of everyone.

snippet.title: Mr. Silly's Song Time
snippet.description: Mr. Silly is a puppet of few words, though his song collection is vast, eclectic, and betrays the sensitive soul within. Thousands upon thousands of B-sides, live recordings and mono versions swirl in his head. To the untrained ear, the world of music Mr. Silly dove into is ostensibly a cacophony of noise. But each lyric, each melody harkens back to a throbbing, still-living memory of his past, and those memories collide, overlap and connect to bring clarity and focus to the shape of his life, just as each part of a symphony comes together in a roiling crescendo of beauty. Also, he fucking hates Ben.

snippet.title: Tricked
snippet.description: Candy-givers, be careful who you provoke on All Hallow's Eve. They may not take too kindly to it.
